package dev.cajeta.unit;

/**
 * Marks a method as a unit test. The `Runner` discovers every `@Test` method
 * across the binary's classes (via `Class.allClasses()` reflection), constructs
 * a fresh instance of the declaring class per method, runs `@BeforeEach` /
 * `@AfterEach` lifecycle around it, and reports pass/fail.
 *
 * ```cajeta
 * class CalculatorTest {
 *     @Test void addsTwoNumbers() { Assert.that(2 + 2).isEqualTo(4); }
 * }
 * ```
 *
 * A test class needs a public no-arg constructor (used to build the per-test
 * instance). A static `@Test` method is invoked without an instance. A thrown
 * `AssertionFailure` — or any other throw — fails the test.
 *
 * Discovery matches the compiler's canonical annotation name `code.Test` (a bare
 * `@Test` use canonicalizes to package `code`); the constant lives in `Runner`.
 */
public annotation Test { }
